description: GFG Resources Inc., a precious metals exploration company, acquires, explores for, and develops gold properties in Canada and the United States. The company holds 100% interests in the Pen gold project covering an area of approximately 445 square kilometers that consists of 162 claims located to the southwest of Timmins, Ontario; and the Dore gold project, which covers an area of approximately 212 square kilometers located in Ontario. It also owns a 100% interest in the Rattlesnake Hills gold project comprising 1,573 unpatented lode mining claims and 8 state mining leases covering an area of approximately 30,400 acres located in Natrona County, Wyoming. The company is headquartered in Saskatoon, Canada.
